Sec. 201.132. HEARING ON VARIANCE PETITION. (a) After
receiving a petition for a variance, a board of adjustment shall
schedule a hearing on the petition and give notice of that hearing.
(b) The directors of the conservation district and the members
of the state board are entitled to appear and be heard at a hearing
on a petition for a variance.
(c) Any owner or occupier of land within the conservation
district who objects to the granting of the variance sought may
intervene and become a party to the proceedings.
(d) A party to a hearing on a petition for a variance may
appear in person or by agent or attorney.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1479, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

